# Triage rubric (apply to every red you encounter)

- **test bug** → fix the spec on this branch. `test(<scope>): fix <name>`.
- **product bug** → finding + `.todo.md` (consumer_role=fixer-<scope>). DO NOT fix the product (unless your archetype is a fixer).
- **spec gap** → log to `docs/open-questions.md` + `.todo.md` (consumer_role=escalate).
- **infra flake** → `--retries=2` + README entry + `.todo.md` only if flake > 1-in-10.

# Self-review (run BEFORE reporting back)

Review your own work against these four categories. Any "no" must be addressed or escalated.

**Completeness**
- [ ] Did I implement everything in the "Done when" criterion?
- [ ] Did I run the gate command listed in Inlined facts?
- [ ] Did the gate command pass?

**Quality**
- [ ] Is this my best work for the budget I had?
- [ ] Are names clear and match what things do (not how they work)?
- [ ] Did `gitnexus_detect_changes` show only the symbols I intended?

**Discipline**
- [ ] Did I stay inside the Files-to-edit list, or did I touch unlisted files?
- [ ] Did I follow YAGNI — only built what was asked?
- [ ] Did I avoid touching anything in the Forbidden paths list?

**Testing**
- [ ] Do the tests I added/touched assert behaviour (not just mock return values)?
- [ ] Did I re-run the failing test from the ticket and confirm it now passes?
- [ ] {{ROLE_SPECIFIC_TESTING_BULLET}}

